# <type>(<scope>): <subject>

#

# <body>

#

# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:

# \* feat: A new feature

# \* fix: A bug fix

# \* docs: Documentation only changes

# \* style: Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code

# \* refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature

# \* perf: A code change that improves performance

# \* test: Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests

# \* build: Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies

# \* ci: Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts

# \* chore: Other changes that don't modify src or test files

# \* revert: Reverts a previous commit

# Scope should be one of the following:

# \* client: Changes to the client/frontend

# \* admin: Changes to the admin-cms

# \* server: Changes to the server/backend

# \* api: Changes to API endpoints

# \* db: Changes to database models or migrations

# \* config: Changes to configuration files

# \* deps: Changes to dependencies

# \* docker: Changes to Docker configuration

# \* deploy: Changes to deployment configuration

# Subject line should:

# \* Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adding")

# \* Be 50 characters or less

# \* Not end with a period

# Body should:

# \* Explain what and why vs. how

# \* Wrap at 72 characters

# \* Use imperative mood

# Footer should contain:

# \* Breaking changes (BREAKING CHANGE: description)

# \* Issue references (Closes #123, Fixes #456)

# Examples:

# feat(client): add user authentication modal

# fix(server): resolve CORS issue with admin endpoints

# docs(api): update API documentation for products

# style(admin): improve dashboard layout responsiveness

# refactor(server): extract email service to separate module

# perf(client): optimize image loading with lazy loading

# test(api): add unit tests for user service

# build(docker): update Node.js to version 18

# ci: add automated deployment workflow

# chore(deps): update dependencies to latest versions
